'''Incontrovertible evidence''' is a colloquial term for [[evidence (law)|evidence]] introduced to prove a fact that is supposed to be so conclusive that there can be no other truth to the matter; evidence so strong it overpowers contrary evidence, directing a fact-finder to a specific and certain conclusion.

Examples: a [[DNA test]] disproving a claim of parenthood.

